Business Brief -- Alitalia S.p.A.:
   Operating Profit Is Posted
   For Second Half of 1991
Revenue totaled 6 trillion lire, up 9.2% from 5.491
trillion lire in 1990.
   The second-half figure allowed the state-run airline to
about break even in terms of operating profit for 1991, the
official said. In the first half of the year, the group
registered a 90.6 billion-lire operating loss.
   Mr. Bisignani didn't give any indications of 1991 net
income figures. Alitalia posted a consolidated loss of 123
billion lire for the first half.